1
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,760
- Who does that room belong to?
- Wai, sir.

2
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:05,440
Wai.

3
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:06,800
Just turn yourself in to the police.

4
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:13,600
White flowers, to say I'm sorry.

5
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,480
<i>Her ex is back to win her over.</i>

6
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:16,960
She might actually be happy about it.

7
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:19,640
- But that man--
- You seem very concerned about her.

8
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,800
I have feelings for you.

9
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:24,160
Know your place.

10
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:24,960
- Come on.
- Stop it!

11
00:02:25,040 --> 00:02:28,400
A full-blown war just to win your heart.
You should be proud.

12
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:34,120
<i>They're becoming more violent,</i>
<i>raiding cargo ships,</i>

13
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:36,800
<i>and slaughtering villagers inland.</i>

14
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:39,760
How can we take them down?
We don't even know where they are.

15
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:58,200
Exactly as I told you, boss.

16
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:01,160
They're moving the supplies at night
to avoid our eyes.

17
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:04,280
Supplies, fuel,

18
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:05,960
and maybe even ammunition, boss.

19
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:08,240
These Japanese soldiers are loaded.

20
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:10,680
Then they should share some with us.

21
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:14,800
Hey, attack.

22
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,640
Why was that so easy?

23
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:46,520
It's a trap. Run!

24
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:36,680
- What's the situation?
- We heard shots fired.

25
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:38,240
The clash has likely started.

26
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,960
This is their only exit route.

27
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:44,520
Stay in position,
and we'll have them cornered.

28
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:46,920
Everyone, get ready.

29
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,080
Hey.

30
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,040
Come on.

31
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:56,600
Uncle Ree, what are you doing?

32
00:04:57,320 --> 00:04:58,240
Hey!

33
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:00,640
Rajit!

34
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:23,080
Boss!

35
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,520
Retreat!

36
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:27,600
After them! Go!

37
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:30,080
- Yes, sir.
- Come on.

38
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:50,600
PHUKET TOWN DISTRICT OFFICE

39
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,840
Here.

40
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:58,560
Thank you.

41
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:09,640
Your plan was brilliant, Mr. Thatri.

42
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,880
Though Black Beard managed to slip away,

43
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:14,120
they'll have to lay low for a while.

44
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:17,640
We should've caught him.

45
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,760
If it weren't for…

46
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,360
Well, how was I supposed to know

47
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:28,240
you were out catching bandits?
If I did, I wouldn't have followed you.

48
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,400
You catch them by being quiet.

49
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:33,120
Did you expect me to say it out loud?

50
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:35,880
You were also being shady, Uncle Ree.

51
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:39,040
My curiosity got the better of me.

52
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:44,280
A good person doesn't wander out
in the middle of the night.

53
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:46,920
Are you calling me a bad person?

54
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,120
Thatri-san didn't mean it like that.

55
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:57,240
He's just worried about you.

56
00:06:57,320 --> 00:07:00,000
He's a bit frustrated
that the opportunity slipped away.

57
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:05,240
We've given Black Beard a serious setback.

58
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:09,360
I doubt those pirates will dare
to show their faces again for a while.

59
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:10,400
Right, District Officer?

60
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,080
I certainly hope so.

61
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:21,240
You're worried about the mastermind
behind Black Beard, aren't you?

62
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,280
Exactly.

63
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:28,240
As long as the mastermind remains free,

64
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:32,880
they'll help Black Beard regroup
and strike again.

65
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,560
All done, boss.

66
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:32,720
We took a heavy hit this time.

67
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:36,039
There's hardly any of us left.
What do we do now, boss?

68
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:38,720
We have to go back and rely on the Master.

69
00:08:38,799 --> 00:08:40,039
Under such protection,

70
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:43,200
we don't have to fear
anyone getting their hands on us.

71
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:48,040
Take us along.
I've served you for ten years,

72
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:50,320
yet I still have no clue
who the Master actually is.

73
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,680
Stay put in the hideout.

74
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,200
Wait until you hear from me.

75
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,120
Is that your way

76
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:06,080
of saying you're leaving us behind?

77
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:10,920
The police and the Japanese
will hunt us down.

78
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,680
Please, let us go with you.

79
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:17,400
Fine.

80
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:21,720
In that case,

81
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:24,520
we'll go fetch some food for you, Boss.

82
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:26,600
Let's go.

83
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,200
I'm sorry.

84
00:09:38,520 --> 00:09:40,720
But the Master's true identity
must remain a secret.

85
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,920
Please, have a look around.

86
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:26,840
Enough with the long face already.

87
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:28,520
I can't focus.

88
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:30,520
Go ahead and shop then.

89
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,600
I didn't say a word.

90
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,000
I'm sorry for scolding you.

91
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,160
Happy now?

92
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:53,200
From now on, I'll remember

93
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:56,520
not to argue with you just to win,

94
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,080
because I know it'll never end.

95
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,320
I was in the wrong too,

96
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:08,280
for following you without asking.

97
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:10,560
It messed up your plans.

98
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:15,720
I'm sorry.

99
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,680
Catching Black Beard is a small matter

100
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:24,760
compared to you getting hurt.

101
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:27,760
Don't ever do this again.

102
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:30,920
I was worried about you, okay?

103
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,320
Uncle Ree,

104
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,760
you were worried about me?

105
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:04,280
Well, you're my niece.

106
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,160
Of course, I'm worried.

107
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:07,720
Why the surprise?

108
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:15,960
I see.

109
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:34,640
I'm only stepping in for Wild Bull.

110
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:36,960
Don't let your thoughts go too far.

111
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:48,960
Here it is, madam.

112
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:03,680
Tri will be delighted
to have this in his hands.

113
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:10,720
Thank you very much, madam.

114
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:13,840
A reward for your hard work.

115
00:13:13,920 --> 00:13:16,000
This is so thorough.

116
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:17,320
Thank you.

117
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:19,040
You're dismissed.

118
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:21,000
I'll take my leave, then.

119
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:46,560
Poj? Hey.

120
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:48,120
Poj!

121
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:50,800
Have you no manners? Give that back.

122
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,720
Mr. Kajorn?

123
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:55,360
Why are you digging into his background?

124
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:57,920
None of your business.

125
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:02,000
Don't say you've found yourself
another little boyfriend.

126
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:05,480
Really, Poj? I have better standards.

127
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:07,080
Don't insult my taste.

128
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:11,800
I certainly believe in your taste.

129
00:14:11,880 --> 00:14:14,120
After all, you chose to marry me.

130
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:22,760
Well then, do as you please.

131
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:26,560
Just as long as you stay away
from Thatri in Chiang Mai,

132
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:27,800
I'm happy.

133
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:34,760
Just leave.

134
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:45,440
And who said anything about Chiang Mai?

135
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:58,240
I can't sell the tin, sir.

136
00:14:58,320 --> 00:15:01,000
I truly don't know

137
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:02,440
where to find the money.

138
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:05,120
Please, give me a couple of months.

139
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:07,920
I'm doing everything I can.

140
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:10,640
What if you still don't have it by then?

141
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:13,880
What will you do?
Won't you just keep pushing the deadline?

142
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:16,680
Letting this slide

143
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:19,880
would set a poor example. How about this?

144
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:24,000
Your house in town,
let's use it as collateral for the debt.

145
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:26,000
If I do that,

146
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:28,600
where am I supposed to live?

147
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:34,120
It's alright. Three months it is.

148
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,920
This war has made life hard for everyone.

149
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:40,800
We should help each other out.

150
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:43,680
Thank you so much, sir.

151
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:46,880
Mr. Thatri,

152
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:49,720
I don't think we should do this.

153
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:51,840
I've made up my mind.

154
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:00,840
Come in.

155
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:05,360
A telegram for you, Mr. Thatri.

156
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:07,520
Thank you, Auntie.

157
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:14,720
In that case, I'll take my leave.

158
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:16,200
Thank you.

159
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,680
Mr. Thatri,

160
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:27,400
Sak might take advantage of your kindness.

161
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:30,920
And it's not just the debtors,

162
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,400
others will start to walk all over you.

163
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:37,320
Who exactly are you referring to?

164
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,160
Mr. Kajorn, of course.

165
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:41,840
He's been in Phuket
for nearly half a month now,

166
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:43,560
showing up here for every meal.

167
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:46,080
Food is expensive during wartime.

168
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:47,800
He's just a drain on our resources.

169
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:49,920
Is it a waste, or are you just jealous?

170
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:56,240
My kindness isn't handed out blindly.

171
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:57,880
However, before I take any action,

172
00:16:57,960 --> 00:16:59,280
I prefer to have solid evidence.

173
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:15,359
You resigned
from the civil service a month ago.

174
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:18,520
I'm not surprised
to see you here every day.

175
00:17:19,599 --> 00:17:22,400
The question is,
why did you keep it a secret?

176
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:24,280
What exactly do you want?

177
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,599
Isn't it obvious, Mr. Thatri?

178
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:28,800
He's a gold digger.

179
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,320
Pretty low-effort of you.

180
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,920
None of your business.

181
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,280
Explain it then, Kajorn.

182
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:40,240
Why did you hide this from us?

183
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:46,680
You haven't broken up with Suda, have you?

184
00:17:46,760 --> 00:17:48,600
You're just here to deceive Rajit

185
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:50,760
and play both sides.

186
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:54,040
That's not true, Rajit.
Suda and I are finished.

187
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:58,000
I kept quiet only to protect her name.

188
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:04,120
Do you really believe him?

189
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:09,640
I swear to you.

190
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:13,280
If I'm lying, may I meet a gruesome end.

191
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:18,880
Suda and I are done.

192
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:21,160
Her jealousy was far too much.

193
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:24,040
She caused such a scene at my office

194
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:25,960
that I was forced to resign in shame.

195
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:29,960
The more I think about it,
the more I realize

196
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:33,480
this is my karma for how I treated you.

197
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:37,360
Now, I want nothing else.

198
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:40,040
All I ask for is your forgiveness, Rajit.

199
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:49,400
Something about this doesn't sit right.

200
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,800
Even if Suda was a backstabbing friend,

201
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:54,880
she's not the kind of person
who behave like that in public.

202
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:58,960
Plus, it sounds like you're just
dumping all the blame on Suda.

203
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:00,960
How are we supposed
to take your word for it?

204
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:03,120
If my oath isn't enough for you,

205
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:06,720
why don't you come to Bangkok
with me and see that I'm not lying.

206
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:12,480
You only dare to say that

207
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:14,840
because you're certain

208
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:20,880
Miss Rajit would never risk getting
involved with your crazy girlfriend.

209
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:24,360
Don't think I can't see right through you.

210
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:28,880
I've said my piece, Rajit.

211
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:31,560
The rest is up to you.

212
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:40,040
What do you think, Uncle Ree?

213
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:46,400
It's your call.

214
00:19:46,480 --> 00:19:48,840
You manage so many businesses,

215
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:52,360
surely you can handle
a situation like this.

216
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:14,560
Wait. Hold on, you guys.

217
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:20,760
Rajit.

218
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:29,880
Hey, you guys.

219
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:33,280
Wait up. Primprao, Nareewan.

220
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:35,240
Wait for me.

221
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:41,120
Is there anything left to say?

222
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:44,080
You just never learn, do you?

223
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:47,480
We really shouldn't have gotten involved.

224
00:20:47,560 --> 00:20:48,920
Uncle Ree warned us.

225
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:51,520
When a couple bickers

226
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:54,640
and then make up,
their friends end up like stray dogs.

227
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:56,880
Could we maybe use a different metaphor?

228
00:21:00,680 --> 00:21:02,480
Please don't be upset.

229
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:05,640
I truly don't have
any feelings left for him.

230
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:08,240
Lies.

231
00:21:08,320 --> 00:21:10,840
If you really felt nothing,
you would have kicked him out.

232
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:14,080
And do you really think he'd just leave?

233
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:19,200
Look, we don't have
any proof that he's lying.

234
00:21:20,040 --> 00:21:22,240
Besides, if I just kick him out,

235
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:24,400
I'll just seem petty.

236
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:26,880
He's lost his job

237
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:28,840
and has no money.

238
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:32,320
How much longer can he afford
to stay here anyway?

239
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,560
You're not the type
to make the same mistake twice, right?

240
00:21:44,360 --> 00:21:45,520
Look,

241
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:47,800
I really don't have feelings
for him anymore.

242
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:49,640
Seriously.

243
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:53,000
Just trust me on this.

244
00:21:56,520 --> 00:21:59,960
I'm not buying that. Your mother
is clearly still attached to him.

245
00:22:01,280 --> 00:22:03,640
After all the help, she still chose this.

246
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:07,080
It's so obvious he's trying to play her.
Is she blind?

247
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:12,640
Stop it. Don't you dare
give me those eyes to defend her.

248
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:16,840
If I meddle any more than this,
I'll end up looking like a stray dog.

249
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:23,920
I didn't mean you, buddy. Just an analogy.

250
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:27,920
Anyway, I'm done.

251
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:30,280
If she wants to be deceived, let her.

252
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:33,200
I'm through with it.

253
00:22:34,800 --> 00:22:36,240
PHRA NAKHON

254
00:22:36,320 --> 00:22:38,040
ELIZABETH HOTEL

255
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:44,360
Ahh! Oh my God!

256
00:22:44,440 --> 00:22:47,200
Tri, it's you!

257
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:49,840
Sri.

258
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:52,280
Tri, it's really you.

259
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:55,640
Finally, you're back to me.

260
00:22:56,880 --> 00:22:58,600
I've missed you so much.

261
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:01,240
Sri,

262
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:02,800
I asked you to come here today

263
00:23:02,880 --> 00:23:04,800
because I have something
to discuss with you.

264
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:15,800
So you only needed a favor?

265
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:17,840
I thought you actually missed me.

266
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:21,080
You're a married woman, Sri.

267
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:24,400
I'd rather not have him
beat me to a pulp again.

268
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:28,240
He refuses to give me a divorce.

269
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:30,800
And I'm not ready to trade my life
to be broke with you.

270
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:32,600
I don't think so.

271
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:35,480
Anyway, you're the person I trust most.

272
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:38,720
Otherwise, I wouldn't have
bothered you with this.

273
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:45,000
Now, that's more like it.

274
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:50,920
But tell me.

275
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:53,880
Why are you so obsessed with this Kajorn?

276
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:57,760
He's just a petty official
who seems like a nobody.

277
00:23:58,760 --> 00:24:00,960
Is he really important enough

278
00:24:01,560 --> 00:24:04,480
for you to travel
all this way from Phuket?

279
00:24:06,640 --> 00:24:08,160
I'm protecting a friend's niece

280
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:09,840
from being conned by this man.

281
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:11,360
Friend's niece, huh?

282
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:14,360
Is it a man or a woman?

283
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:17,640
If it's a woman, is she pretty?

284
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:22,160
My friend's niece is like my own family.

285
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:24,000
Why would you ask that?

286
00:24:25,520 --> 00:24:28,200
I don't care. I have to stay on guard.

287
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:36,000
According to my detective,

288
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:40,080
Kajorn already has a wife.
But they aren't legally married.

289
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:42,800
Finding her won't be easy,

290
00:24:44,080 --> 00:24:46,360
but my wealth can open a lot of doors.

291
00:24:56,960 --> 00:24:57,800
He's not here?

292
00:24:57,880 --> 00:25:01,520
Did he mention
where he was headed or for how long?

293
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:04,320
He didn't say. Just said he had
some business to take care of.

294
00:25:05,320 --> 00:25:07,200
But Mr. Thatri only packed a few things.

295
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:09,720
I'm sure he'll be back within the week.

296
00:25:11,480 --> 00:25:14,480
Oh, Uncle Ree. We live in the same house,

297
00:25:14,560 --> 00:25:16,440
yet he tells me nothing.

298
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:19,240
If I hadn't realized
I hadn't seen him all day,

299
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:20,600
I'd still be in the dark.

300
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:24,160
Haven't seen who?
Surely you don't mean me, do you?

301
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:29,640
What do you want, Kajorn?

302
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:33,040
I wanted to invite you to the beach.

303
00:25:33,120 --> 00:25:36,720
I've been in Phuket for nearly 20 days,
and I still haven't seen the waves.

304
00:25:38,720 --> 00:25:39,560
I'm sorry,

305
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:42,280
but I already have plans
with Primprao and Nareewan.

306
00:25:42,360 --> 00:25:44,040
I won't be able to join you.

307
00:25:44,680 --> 00:25:45,800
Excuse me.

308
00:25:50,480 --> 00:25:52,120
Who is your boss so angry at?

309
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:53,720
Why did she just ditch me like that?

310
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:57,280
It's probably Mr. Thatri, sir.

311
00:25:57,360 --> 00:26:00,480
He left without a word,
so she's not in the best of moods.

312
00:26:00,560 --> 00:26:02,000
- Nid!
- Ouch.

313
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:04,680
He's not our boss.
You don't need to answer every question.

314
00:26:04,760 --> 00:26:06,160
Understood.

315
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:09,800
You old hag.
How dare you speak to me like that?

316
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:38,360
Have you been waiting long, Rajit?

317
00:26:38,440 --> 00:26:39,360
Ages.

318
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:46,480
I'm so sorry.

319
00:26:46,560 --> 00:26:49,320
I had to help my dad finish the accounts
before I could slip away.

320
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:52,960
And I just got back
from the temple with my mom.

321
00:26:53,040 --> 00:26:56,760
Hey, it's not even noon yet.
Are you hungry already?

322
00:26:56,840 --> 00:26:58,760
I can be hungry whenever I want.

323
00:26:58,840 --> 00:27:01,320
I'm starving, and I'm fuming.

324
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:26,240
Are you possessed by a gluttonous spirit?
Your stomach is going to explode.

325
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:30,160
Listen, I haven't settled my score
with Uncle Ree yet.

326
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:31,640
I'm not going to die that easily.

327
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:38,200
You two seem close lately.

328
00:27:39,480 --> 00:27:42,440
Is his absence really enough
to make you this upset?

329
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:47,080
What?

330
00:27:47,160 --> 00:27:49,680
Well, it's just that we work together.

331
00:27:49,760 --> 00:27:53,120
Leaving without a word
and dumping all the work on me.

332
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,120
It's irresponsible.

333
00:28:03,840 --> 00:28:05,520
- What?
- There's a fight breaking out.

334
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:06,800
- Let's see.
- What's going on?

335
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:08,440
- What?
- There's a fight.

336
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:09,400
- Here.
- Agh!

337
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:11,360
- Pay up right now.
- Like hell I will.

338
00:28:11,440 --> 00:28:12,760
Give me my money.

339
00:28:12,840 --> 00:28:14,640
Pay up right now.

340
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:20,800
Pay me.

341
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:24,360
What's happened?

342
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:27,760
That's enough.

343
00:28:27,840 --> 00:28:29,640
<i>So, how is my niece?</i>

344
00:28:30,320 --> 00:28:32,680
All I know is she's got half the assets,

345
00:28:32,760 --> 00:28:36,360
but I've never actually met her.
I'm curious to know what she's like.

346
00:28:41,640 --> 00:28:42,960
Don't even get me started.

347
00:28:43,640 --> 00:28:44,760
That girl is a handful,

348
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:46,880
a total firecracker.

349
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:49,240
She's arrogant, stubborn.

350
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:51,920
Despite being so young,
all she does is talk back.

351
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:53,760
Sometimes I just want
to teach her a lesson.

352
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,440
That bad, huh?

353
00:28:57,800 --> 00:29:00,240
My niece is that awful?

354
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:02,080
I had no idea

355
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:04,680
she'd have such a terrible attitude.

356
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:06,960
I'm so sorry, man,

357
00:29:07,040 --> 00:29:09,600
for forcing you
to live with someone like that.

358
00:29:12,640 --> 00:29:13,880
She's not that bad.

359
00:29:15,160 --> 00:29:17,040
Rajit has her virtues.

360
00:29:20,720 --> 00:29:21,640
She's sharp,

361
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:25,440
quick-witted, kind,

362
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:27,240
and sympathetic.

363
00:29:30,040 --> 00:29:31,920
Being around her is quite comforting.

364
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:34,720
Also, she's hard-working,

365
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:36,720
and her desserts are delicious.

366
00:29:39,400 --> 00:29:41,600
Are you praising her or insulting her?

367
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:44,640
That's the opposite of what you just said.

368
00:29:48,600 --> 00:29:50,440
The bottom line is, she's a decent woman.

369
00:29:52,360 --> 00:29:53,200
Wait a minute.

370
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:57,200
Do you have a crush on my niece?

371
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:01,480
Hey. Don't talk nonsense.

372
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:08,160
Anyway, when are you going to recover,

373
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:09,560
so that you can get back to Phuket?

374
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:14,360
Look at me, man.
Do I look like I can go anywhere?

375
00:30:15,760 --> 00:30:16,760
The sooner the better.

376
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:19,840
I don't know how much longer
I can keep dealing with your relatives.

377
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:24,600
But you've been doing a great job.

378
00:30:25,280 --> 00:30:26,760
Even my mom is impressed with you.

379
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:34,160
- So, how is it?
- Hmm.

380
00:30:34,240 --> 00:30:36,720
Delicious. This place
is as good as always.

381
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:47,240
Hey. Rajit,

382
00:30:47,320 --> 00:30:49,040
are you okay?

383
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:53,240
Yeah, you've gone completely pale.

384
00:30:56,160 --> 00:30:57,000
Well,

385
00:30:57,680 --> 00:30:59,840
I feel a bit lightheaded.

386
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:05,840
Anyway, where should we head next?

387
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:12,400
In your condition?
You aren't going anywhere.

388
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:13,800
- Let's get you home.
- Yeah.

389
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:15,600
I agree.

390
00:31:21,320 --> 00:31:22,720
Probably for the best.

391
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:24,520
Excuse me.

392
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:26,720
- Check please.
- Alright.

393
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:30,200
Are you alright?

394
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:38,960
Here.

395
00:31:40,480 --> 00:31:42,080
One moment, please.

396
00:31:51,400 --> 00:31:52,880
- What?
- A fight broke out!

397
00:31:52,960 --> 00:31:54,160
- Let's see.
- What's going on?

398
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:55,800
- What?
- There's a fight.

399
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:57,240
- Pay up right now.
- Like hell I will.

400
00:31:57,320 --> 00:31:58,640
Give me my money.

401
00:31:58,720 --> 00:31:59,680
- What happened?
- Pay up.

402
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:09,400
Pay up!

403
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:11,040
What happened?

404
00:32:35,320 --> 00:32:37,200
Sir.

405
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:43,440
Here.

406
00:32:43,520 --> 00:32:46,880
The money for the fight
you and your friend put on earlier.

407
00:32:46,960 --> 00:32:48,320
Thank you very much, sir.

408
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:50,280
And here's for the next job.

409
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:53,680
I want you to snatch that woman's purse.

410
00:32:54,800 --> 00:32:56,680
- That one over there.
- Yes, sir.

411
00:32:56,760 --> 00:33:00,560
Once you get it, run as far as you can.
You got that?

412
00:33:00,640 --> 00:33:01,800
Understood, sir.

413
00:33:04,120 --> 00:33:06,240
Thank you again, sir.

414
00:33:20,920 --> 00:33:22,800
RUNG RUENG EATERY

415
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:35,840
Rajit, are you okay?

416
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:39,080
Rajit, are you okay?

417
00:33:45,040 --> 00:33:46,160
I'm fine.

418
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:49,000
If it's too much,
let's go sit down for a bit.

419
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:53,640
Oh, don't worry. I'm okay.

420
00:34:02,560 --> 00:34:04,280
Hey! Thief!

421
00:34:04,360 --> 00:34:07,080
- Stop right there, you scum!
- Help!

422
00:34:07,160 --> 00:34:09,440
Somebody help! Thief!

423
00:34:10,639 --> 00:34:12,520
Rajit, stay right here.

424
00:34:12,600 --> 00:34:13,760
I'll be right back.

425
00:34:42,239 --> 00:34:43,080
Here's your bag.

426
00:34:44,320 --> 00:34:45,480
Thanks.

427
00:34:47,679 --> 00:34:49,120
That thief was bizarre.

428
00:34:49,199 --> 00:34:51,440
Instead of keeping the bag,

429
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:55,120
he just tossed it aside
the moment he saw me chasing.

430
00:34:55,199 --> 00:34:56,480
I agree.

431
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:05,000
Where did Rajit go?

432
00:35:06,160 --> 00:35:07,240
What?

433
00:35:07,320 --> 00:35:09,040
Did she faint and collapse somewhere?

434
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:17,200
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

435
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:19,320
Did you see the friend we were with?

436
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:21,400
Oh, the pretty young lady?

437
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:23,840
I saw her faint,
but I saw someone help her.

438
00:35:24,840 --> 00:35:26,640
Someone already helped her?

439
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:28,640
Who helped her?

440
00:35:28,720 --> 00:35:31,240
I'm not really sure.
I just assumed they were with you.

441
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:32,960
Who?

442
00:35:33,720 --> 00:35:35,120
What do we do?

443
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:38,560
Rajit.

444
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:41,280
What do we do?

445
00:35:41,360 --> 00:35:43,120
Miss Primprao. Miss Nareewan.

446
00:35:43,800 --> 00:35:44,920
Mr. Vijarn!

447
00:35:45,520 --> 00:35:46,800
Is something wrong?

448
00:35:46,880 --> 00:35:47,960
Please help us.

449
00:35:48,040 --> 00:35:50,280
Someone has taken Rajit away.

450
00:35:50,360 --> 00:35:51,400
What did you say?

451
00:35:52,120 --> 00:35:54,880
In that case, we need to start searching.
Where did you last see her?

452
00:35:54,960 --> 00:35:56,120
- Right here.
- Right here.

453
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:12,680
So arrogant, huh?

454
00:36:13,560 --> 00:36:14,960
Ever since you dumped me,

455
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:17,560
you've had men lining up for you.

456
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:21,800
But from now on,

457
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:26,280
both you and your fortune

458
00:36:28,200 --> 00:36:29,680
belong to me.

459
00:36:37,840 --> 00:36:39,160
It's hot.

460
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:13,200
Of all the times for an air raid, why now?

461
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:17,520
- Miss Rajit!
- Rajit!

462
00:37:17,600 --> 00:37:20,000
- Miss Rajit!
- Rajit!

463
00:37:20,080 --> 00:37:21,680
<i>Emergency alert.</i>

464
00:37:21,760 --> 00:37:22,960
<i>Emergency alert.</i>

465
00:37:26,280 --> 00:37:27,320
Dammit!

466
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:33,200
- Can you hear us?
- Have you seen a girl with--

467
00:37:33,280 --> 00:37:34,120
I don't. I must run.

468
00:37:34,200 --> 00:37:35,600
- Be careful.
- Miss Rajit!

469
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:37,120
- Rajit!
- Miss Rajit!

470
00:37:37,720 --> 00:37:38,680
- Rajit!
- Have you seen--

471
00:37:54,760 --> 00:37:55,640
Beware!

472
00:37:56,160 --> 00:37:57,480
- Rajit!
- Have you seen--

473
00:37:57,560 --> 00:37:58,800
Rajit!

474
00:37:59,400 --> 00:38:00,520
Take cover!

475
00:38:01,080 --> 00:38:02,080
Run!

476
00:38:02,840 --> 00:38:04,240
- Miss Rajit!
- Where is she?

477
00:38:04,320 --> 00:38:06,520
The war will begin soon.

478
00:38:06,600 --> 00:38:08,560
I should never have
chased after that thief.

479
00:38:08,640 --> 00:38:11,280
If we can't find her,
I'll never be able to forgive myself.

480
00:38:11,360 --> 00:38:13,040
Both of you, please stay calm.

481
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:15,240
I will not let anything happen to her.

482
00:38:15,320 --> 00:38:16,840
Let's keep looking.

483
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:18,400
- Miss Rajit!
- Rajit!

484
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:37,400
Are you okay? Calm down! Stick together!

485
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:50,400
<i>Miss Rajit!</i>

486
00:38:59,720 --> 00:39:01,000
<i>Miss Rajit!</i>

487
00:39:05,360 --> 00:39:07,840
PHRA NAKHON

488
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:10,400
Speak of the devil.

489
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:14,080
I finally get to see you in person.

490
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:16,680
Mother Suang.

491
00:39:16,760 --> 00:39:18,600
I'm glad to meet you.

492
00:39:21,360 --> 00:39:23,000
Thank you so much

493
00:39:23,080 --> 00:39:25,400
for finally clearing my name.

494
00:39:27,640 --> 00:39:28,640
Don't mention it.

495
00:39:29,240 --> 00:39:31,120
My friend's mother is like my own mother.

496
00:39:34,960 --> 00:39:37,040
Spoken like a true Leopard.

497
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:39,600
Didn't I tell you, Mom?
Do you believe me now?

498
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:46,880
Thank you so much.

499
00:39:55,720 --> 00:39:57,080
<i>My beloved Sasitorn,</i>

500
00:39:57,720 --> 00:39:59,720
<i>the special assignment I've been given</i>

501
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:03,200
<i>might take quite a while to complete.</i>
<i>I'm lucky to have a partner</i>

502
00:40:03,280 --> 00:40:07,280
<i>who is a well-known socialite</i>
<i>with incredible skills,</i>

503
00:40:07,360 --> 00:40:10,200
<i>from marksmanship</i>
<i>and boxing to horse riding.</i>

504
00:40:12,120 --> 00:40:13,160
That sounds so familiar.

505
00:40:15,760 --> 00:40:17,680
<i>He gives me hope.</i>

506
00:40:18,320 --> 00:40:19,680
<i>Once this work is finished,</i>

507
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:22,520
<i>I'll request an immediate transfer</i>
<i>back to Bangkok.</i>

508
00:40:22,600 --> 00:40:26,160
<i>Then, we can finally get married</i>
<i>and start our family.</i>

509
00:40:27,280 --> 00:40:28,120
<i>I love you</i>

510
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:30,120
<i>with every breath I take.</i>

511
00:40:34,160 --> 00:40:36,120
You've loved the wrong person.

512
00:40:38,040 --> 00:40:39,480
I'm just a coward.

513
00:40:40,200 --> 00:40:42,160
I'm not worthy of your love at all.

514
00:41:02,040 --> 00:41:04,680
Rajit. How are you feeling?

515
00:41:04,760 --> 00:41:07,240
We're worried about you.

516
00:41:09,320 --> 00:41:10,600
Let me help you.

517
00:41:18,640 --> 00:41:21,480
Miss Rajit, I was so worried.

518
00:41:22,600 --> 00:41:25,000
Even if the American
and Japanese armies were at war,

519
00:41:25,600 --> 00:41:27,080
I would never stop searching for you.

520
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:30,880
Your life is more important than my own.

521
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:41,400
Rajit, who were you with?

522
00:41:41,480 --> 00:41:45,080
The waiter at the restaurant said
someone took you away.

523
00:41:46,600 --> 00:41:49,120
Who? I didn't go anywhere with anyone.

524
00:41:50,480 --> 00:41:51,640
Wait,

525
00:41:51,720 --> 00:41:53,440
you don't remember anything at all?

526
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:58,080
I only remember standing
outside the restaurant.

527
00:41:58,160 --> 00:42:01,120
Next thing I know,
I'm waking up right here.

528
00:42:02,880 --> 00:42:04,440
This means

529
00:42:04,520 --> 00:42:07,120
someone is definitely
out to get you again.

530
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:14,400
If that's the case, you're in real danger.

531
00:42:15,040 --> 00:42:17,960
I agree, Miss Rajit.
This is a very serious matter.

532
00:42:18,040 --> 00:42:21,000
From now on, if you need to go anywhere,

533
00:42:21,080 --> 00:42:22,400
please let me take you.

534
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:36,960
Um, Mr. Vijarn? I think Rajit

535
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:38,800
really needs some peace and quiet.

536
00:42:39,440 --> 00:42:41,160
Since she's safe now,

537
00:42:41,240 --> 00:42:43,160
let's not disturb her any further.

538
00:42:45,680 --> 00:42:47,120
Let's head out, Mr. Vijarn.

539
00:42:49,040 --> 00:42:50,840
Make sure you rest well, Miss Rajit.

540
00:42:51,920 --> 00:42:53,160
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

541
00:42:53,240 --> 00:42:55,120
Make sure to cover yourself
with a blanket.

542
00:43:43,360 --> 00:43:46,960
Don Jose. How did you get here?

543
00:43:53,480 --> 00:43:55,840
Your owner just vanished.

544
00:43:55,920 --> 00:43:57,760
He didn't even tell me where he was going.

545
00:44:01,680 --> 00:44:03,160
Without Uncle Ree

546
00:44:03,960 --> 00:44:05,600
and Grandpa,

547
00:44:06,640 --> 00:44:08,560
this house doesn't feel like home anymore.

548
00:44:40,400 --> 00:44:41,680
How are you?

549
00:44:43,160 --> 00:44:44,280
My Sasi…

550
00:45:06,400 --> 00:45:08,280
Stop making that face.

551
00:45:09,080 --> 00:45:11,480
I'm so tired of seeing it.

552
00:45:13,640 --> 00:45:15,600
I just feel so guilty.

553
00:45:15,680 --> 00:45:17,520
Stop with the guilt.

554
00:45:17,600 --> 00:45:19,480
Once he returns,

555
00:45:19,560 --> 00:45:21,320
you are going to marry him.

556
00:45:21,400 --> 00:45:23,120
- But--
- I told you to stop.

557
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:25,360
That's all in the past now.

558
00:45:25,440 --> 00:45:29,200
We can't go back. We have to move forward.

559
00:45:29,280 --> 00:45:31,000
Do you understand?

560
00:45:32,360 --> 00:45:34,280
Yes, Mother.

561
00:46:57,680 --> 00:46:59,880
Take this to the hotel.

562
00:46:59,960 --> 00:47:01,800
And make sure nobody catches you.

563
00:47:01,880 --> 00:47:02,960
Yes, madam.

564
00:47:21,360 --> 00:47:24,080
I've got you now, Tri.

565
00:47:25,520 --> 00:47:28,360
Thatri? That bastard again?

566
00:47:30,840 --> 00:47:32,560
Here's a letter from Miss Srichan, sir.

567
00:47:34,040 --> 00:47:35,440
Thank you.

568
00:47:42,560 --> 00:47:44,400
<i>This afternoon at three,</i>

569
00:47:44,480 --> 00:47:47,000
<i>I'll be waiting for you in my hotel room.</i>

570
00:47:47,080 --> 00:47:49,440
<i>I'll tell the receptionist</i>

571
00:47:49,520 --> 00:47:51,360
<i>to show you the way.</i>

572
00:47:51,440 --> 00:47:53,480
<i>Don't you hesitate, Tri.</i>

573
00:47:53,560 --> 00:47:56,440
<i>I've obtained some vital information.</i>

574
00:47:57,080 --> 00:48:00,400
<i>If you don't show up, you'll regret it.</i>

575
00:48:03,360 --> 00:48:05,400
Why do we have to talk in a hotel room?

576
00:48:21,240 --> 00:48:23,920
- Sri…
- Hi, Tri.

577
00:48:24,000 --> 00:48:25,960
Darling…

578
00:48:26,880 --> 00:48:28,200
What are you doing there?

579
00:48:28,280 --> 00:48:30,120
I thought you had vital information?

580
00:48:41,360 --> 00:48:42,960
Before you get the info,

581
00:48:44,240 --> 00:48:46,880
you have to give me something in return.

582
00:48:49,480 --> 00:48:53,320
I can't just do all the work
for you for free, right?

583
00:49:01,400 --> 00:49:03,360
Sri, stop it right there.

584
00:49:03,440 --> 00:49:05,240
I don't wanna get thrashed by Poj again.

585
00:49:05,880 --> 00:49:08,960
Oh, Tri…

586
00:49:17,400 --> 00:49:20,680
Here it is. The address
of Suda, Kajorn's wife.

587
00:49:45,200 --> 00:49:46,520
If you want it,

588
00:49:47,760 --> 00:49:49,000
come and get it.

589
00:49:53,080 --> 00:49:56,200
Wanting to rekindle our old flame, huh?

590
00:50:01,800 --> 00:50:05,080
Is that a yes or a no?

591
00:50:19,520 --> 00:50:21,440
Thatri, you're a dead man.

592
00:50:25,240 --> 00:50:26,080
Thatri.

593
00:50:34,120 --> 00:50:35,760
Make it feel like our old days.

594
00:50:35,840 --> 00:50:38,200
Like when we were dating

595
00:50:38,880 --> 00:50:40,720
back in England.

596
00:50:46,800 --> 00:50:47,920
Let's take it to the top.

597
00:50:48,520 --> 00:50:51,280
Like we're on the peak of Mount Everest?

598
00:50:55,920 --> 00:50:57,560
That's a bit too cold for me.

599
00:50:57,640 --> 00:50:59,720
I prefer it hot.

600
00:51:00,320 --> 00:51:03,960
I'd rather be at the very tip of a pyramid

601
00:51:04,040 --> 00:51:05,840
in Egypt.

602
00:51:09,960 --> 00:51:11,760
Then don't keep me waiting.

603
00:51:13,040 --> 00:51:14,840
I'm already starting to feel the heat.

604
00:51:24,360 --> 00:51:25,560
Open up, Thatri!

605
00:51:25,640 --> 00:51:28,160
Thatri! Get your ass out here right now!

606
00:51:28,240 --> 00:51:29,800
Get out here!

607
00:51:32,760 --> 00:51:35,280
I'm going to count to five.
If he's not out by then,

608
00:51:35,360 --> 00:51:37,760
break down the door
and beat him to a pulp.

609
00:51:37,840 --> 00:51:39,000
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

610
00:51:41,480 --> 00:51:43,360
Sri, put your clothes on.

611
00:51:43,440 --> 00:51:45,200
He's definitely going to stomp me.

612
00:51:45,280 --> 00:51:46,840
Five!

613
00:51:47,920 --> 00:51:49,320
Sir.

614
00:51:49,400 --> 00:51:51,160
What happened to one through four?

615
00:51:51,240 --> 00:51:52,800
I'm in no mood for counting.

616
00:51:57,320 --> 00:51:58,880
Open up!

617
00:51:59,560 --> 00:52:01,320
Open up.

618
00:52:03,640 --> 00:52:07,080
Tri. I think you need
to jump out the window.

619
00:52:07,160 --> 00:52:09,160
- Go.
- Wait, Sri.

620
00:52:09,240 --> 00:52:12,440
This is the fifth floor.
I wouldn't survive that fall.

621
00:52:12,520 --> 00:52:13,560
I'm not doing that.

622
00:52:13,640 --> 00:52:15,480
Then what are you going to do?

623
00:52:17,000 --> 00:52:18,600
Is that all the strength you've got?

624
00:52:18,680 --> 00:52:19,800
Yes, sir.

625
00:52:21,200 --> 00:52:22,000
Open up.

626
00:52:23,760 --> 00:52:26,520
Break it down. I'll pay for the damages.

627
00:52:28,160 --> 00:52:29,280
- Open up.
- Do it now.

628
00:52:29,360 --> 00:52:30,960
I said open up!

629
00:52:37,040 --> 00:52:40,080
Excuse me, sir.
It's been exactly half an hour.

630
00:52:50,760 --> 00:52:52,600
- Hey, kid.
- Yes, sir?

631
00:52:55,080 --> 00:52:58,040
If an old man shows up
asking for Thatri or Srichan,

632
00:52:58,120 --> 00:52:59,800
redirect him to another floor entirely.

633
00:53:01,000 --> 00:53:02,640
Then, in exactly half an hour,

634
00:53:02,720 --> 00:53:04,960
come and knock loudly on my door.

635
00:53:06,000 --> 00:53:06,840
Understood, sir.

636
00:53:10,120 --> 00:53:11,040
Thank you, Sri.

637
00:53:11,120 --> 00:53:14,640
Hey. Tri, did you just play me?

638
00:53:15,280 --> 00:53:17,360
I'm heading out. See you around.

639
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:22,120
I'll be going now, madam.

640
00:53:24,120 --> 00:53:25,680
You are such a sly fox, Tri.

641
00:53:27,280 --> 00:53:28,840
There's no one here, sir.

642
00:53:32,600 --> 00:53:34,280
Track him down.

643
00:53:34,360 --> 00:53:35,800
I'm going to kill him.

644
00:53:35,880 --> 00:53:37,920
Yes, sir. Let's go.

645
00:53:43,400 --> 00:53:46,680
PHUKET

646
00:54:12,320 --> 00:54:13,800
Where have you been?

647
00:54:17,920 --> 00:54:19,720
Gone where?

648
00:54:20,640 --> 00:54:21,800
Who are you looking for?

649
00:54:27,520 --> 00:54:30,920
Don't tell me…
you're waiting for Uncle Ree.

650
00:54:40,760 --> 00:54:42,600
Look at you.

651
00:54:43,240 --> 00:54:45,120
You're totally missing him.

652
00:54:50,440 --> 00:54:52,680
Who? Who's missing him?

653
00:54:52,760 --> 00:54:54,600
I didn't miss him.

654
00:54:54,680 --> 00:54:56,440
I'm just annoyed at him.

655
00:54:56,520 --> 00:54:58,080
He just vanished

656
00:54:58,160 --> 00:55:00,960
and left me buried in a pile of work.

657
00:55:02,120 --> 00:55:04,120
What an irresponsible person.

658
00:55:07,480 --> 00:55:09,240
I hope you mean what you say.

659
00:55:10,040 --> 00:55:13,600
Because lately, you've been
suspiciously nice to Uncle Ree.

660
00:55:15,240 --> 00:55:16,600
Hey,

661
00:55:16,680 --> 00:55:19,920
if you don't believe me,
go sleep at your own houses.

662
00:55:20,000 --> 00:55:21,480
You don't have to keep me company.

663
00:55:21,560 --> 00:55:24,280
You claim you're staying here
because you're worried about me,

664
00:55:25,120 --> 00:55:27,400
but you just want to see
Uncle Ree yourselves.

665
00:55:29,920 --> 00:55:32,440
Look at that, our Rajit is sulking.

666
00:55:37,280 --> 00:55:40,160
There, there. Don't be mad.

667
00:55:40,240 --> 00:55:43,440
We're here because we care about you.

668
00:55:43,520 --> 00:55:45,960
Uncle Ree is just a bonus.

669
00:55:46,640 --> 00:55:48,920
If he doesn't show up, who cares, right?

670
00:55:51,760 --> 00:55:54,480
Please, don't be mad.

671
00:55:56,400 --> 00:55:57,760
I'm not even mad.

672
00:56:02,000 --> 00:56:03,320
You sure about that?

673
00:56:05,560 --> 00:56:06,600
Yes, really.

674
00:56:09,440 --> 00:56:11,400
You really are a terrible liar.

675
00:56:11,920 --> 00:56:13,400
I'm not lying.

676
00:56:14,080 --> 00:56:16,040
Okay, whatever.

677
00:56:16,120 --> 00:56:21,680
PHRA NAKHON

678
00:56:44,720 --> 00:56:46,120
Is anyone home?

679
00:56:47,400 --> 00:56:48,960
I'm looking for Miss Suda.

680
00:57:14,840 --> 00:57:17,480
If Uncle Ree can eat it, so can I.

681
00:57:21,200 --> 00:57:23,840
Good heavens. How scandalous.

682
00:57:24,720 --> 00:57:26,520
Good grief.

683
00:57:27,560 --> 00:57:29,480
<i>The lowest point of my life</i>

684
00:57:30,200 --> 00:57:32,440
<i>all started with that man named Kajorn.</i>

685
00:57:32,520 --> 00:57:34,480
Even if Rajit kicks me out, I'm not going.

686
00:57:34,560 --> 00:57:36,240
You pathetic pimp.

687
00:57:39,000 --> 00:57:41,240
<i>I don't care about</i>
<i>the situation with Suda,</i>

688
00:57:41,320 --> 00:57:44,040
but if you lay a finger on Rajit,
you're a dead man.

689
00:57:47,160 --> 00:57:48,040
Help me.

690
00:58:18,480 --> 00:58:20,480
Subtitle translation by:
Khathathong Thongtumlueng
